  "prompt": "Do employees at National Beverage have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "Work-life balance at National Beverage, like in many companies, can vary significantly depending on the specific role, department, and individual circumstances. \n\nIn general:\n- **Corporate roles:** Employees in these positions might experience a more standard workweek with potential flexibility for remote work, depending on company policy. Corporate roles may offer a better work-life balance than manufacturing or sales roles.\n- **Manufacturing and Operations:** These positions might involve shift work, which can affect work-life balance. Employees may have to work nights, weekends, or overtime, impacting their ability to maintain a consistent work-life balance.\n- **Sales and Distribution:** These roles might require travel, long hours, and meeting sales targets, which can put pressure on personal time. \n\nVarious factors, such as management practices, company culture, and specific job requirements, will also influence work-life balance. Additionally, individual experiences can differ widely even within the same department, based on personal expectations and priorities. \n\nFor the most accurate and detailed information, potential employees should seek feedback from current or former employees through networking platforms like LinkedIn or review sites like Glassdoor.",
